12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12
13 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
13
14 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 301 of Title 41, unless there is
14
15 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
15
16 A. For the purposes of this section:
16
17 1. “Landlord” means the owner, lessor, or sublessor of a
17
18 residential or nonresidential property including, but not limited
18
19 to, the dwelling unit or the building of which it is a part,
19
20 manufactured or mobile home site, space, or lot; provided, it also
20
21 means a manager of the premises who fails to comply with the
21
22 disclosure provisions of Section 116 of Title 41 of the Oklahoma
22
23 Statutes;
23
24
24
