1 2. “Tenant” means any person entitled under a rental agreement
1
2 to occupy a residential or nonresidential property; and
2
3 3. “Utility” means any corporation, association, company, or
3
4 individuals, or their trustees, lessees, or receivers, successors or
4
5 assigns, including cities, towns, or other bodies politic, that own,
5
6 operate, or manage any plant or equipment, or any part thereof,
6
7 directly or indirectly, for public use, or may supply or furnish gas
7
8 by pipeline, heat or light with gas, electric current for light,
8
9 heat, or power, or water for power or domestic purposes.
9
10 B. Notwithstanding any other provision of law, no utility
10
11 operating in this state shall hold a landlord liable for bills,
11
12 fees, or charges for services accrued by a tenant occupying a
12
13 residential or nonresidential property otherwise owned or maintained
13
14 by the landlord.
14
15 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
